<h2>What is Schema Markup and Why Does it Matter for Hills District Businesses?</h2>

<p>Schema markup is a form of structured data that you add to your website's HTML code to help search engines understand your content better. Think of it as a translator between your website and Google – it tells search engines exactly what your content means, not just what it says.</p>

<p>For local businesses in the Hills District, schema markup is particularly powerful because it helps you appear in rich snippets, local pack results, and knowledge panels. When someone searches for "electrician near Baulkham Hills" or "best restaurant Castle Hill," schema markup helps Google understand that your business is relevant to their query and should be prominently displayed.</p>

